Title: Junior Front-End Software Engineer
Description:
Narrativ uses near-perfect human voices generated by machine learning to create and read podcast-quality audio versions of existing newspaper articles that can support ads.

We Have 4 Distinct Products

We believe that Narrativ can create an entirely new class of audio content for people to consume that meets their current consumption preferences. In the last decade, readership has plunged in the face of listenership, and we want to be the entity that enables consumers to listen to anything that was previously limited to written form.

An integrated player that can serve audio directly on publisher websites
A mobile app that aggregates audio content across all of our publisher partners
An audio ad platform that we use to create unique copy for many different audiences
A publisher platform that our partners can use to track the performance of their narrated content

Who You Are

The Junior Front-End Software Engineer position will be responsible for maintaining, improving, and tailoring our existing front-end codebase. This may include: tidy/refactor of existing integrated players; deploying integrated player to new publishers (e.g., tweaking CSS/HTML to work within variety of platforms); adding new features/functionality (e.g., new behaviors to the player).

This role will start focused on execution in the publisher-integrated player and may evolve into ownership of this component. This role will likely also contribute to the ad/publisher platform, and depending on personal interest, the mobile app.

This employee will work closely with the CTO in order to create the best user experience possible.

Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in computer science or related technical field
Strong knowledge of UI / UX
0-2 years of working experience as a front-end software engineer
Excellent communication skills
Strong interest or previous experience in audio / data is a plus

Languages / Framework

Vanilla HTML + CSS + Javascript
React
(Flutter optional, but a plus if this individual would also like to be involved with mobile app)

Compensation Range

Salary: $85K - $120K
Equity: 0.1% - 0.5%

Other Benefits!

Choose from 3 different Medical, Dental, Vision plans
80% covered medical premiums for employees
Unlimited PTO
401k program + 4% match
Up to $500 stipend for home office set up
Meetups a couple of times a month/quarter
On and offsite team building events
And other perks as the company continues to scale!

Title: Machine Learning Engineer - Genetic & Epigenetic Cardiovascular
Description:
About Cardio Diagnostics:

 

Cardio Diagnostics is a precision cardiovascular medicine company dedicated to making cardiovascular disease prevention and early detection more accessible, personalized, and precise. Our mission is to further develop and commercialize our proprietary Artificial Intelligence (AI)-driven Integrated Epigenetic-Genetic Engine™ (“Core Technology”) for cardiovascular disease, positioning ourselves as one of the leading medical technology companies enabling improved prevention, early detection, diagnostics and assisting in the treatment of cardiovascular disease.

 

Qualifications

●     PhD or MS degree in a quantitative discipline (e.g. computer science, biomedical informatics, machine learning, statistics, computational biology, applied mathematics, physics, or similar)

●     3+ years of relevant industry experience

●     Outstanding analytical and problem solving skills, with a particular focus on understanding the intricacies of multi-modal medical data sets

●     Experience working with clinical and genomic data

●     Expert-level experience with supervised, self-supervised and unsupervised machine learning algorithms, such as: regression, generative modeling, deep neural networks, gradient boosting, non-linear low dimensional embeddings and clustering

●     Proficient in Python, Sklearn and SQL

●     Strong programming skills

●     Experience in a fast-paced, entrepreneurial environment

●     Ability to effectively communicate complex plans and technical information to stakeholders with diverse backgrounds

●     Highly self-motivated and directed individual with a strong work ethic

 

Preferred Qualifications

●     Strong peer-reviewed publication record

●     Familiarity with cloud computing services such as AWS

●     Experience building machine learning based models towards cardiovascular outcomes

 

Responsibilities

●     Analyze and integrate large diverse clinical and molecular and datasets to extract insights, and drive research opportunities

●     Design and prototype novel analysis tools and algorithms for biomarker mining, predicting patient outcome and treatment response

●     Collaborate with product, science, engineering, and business development teams to build the most advanced data platform in precision medicine

●     Interrogate analytical results for robustness, validity, and out of sample stability

●     Document, summarize, and present your findings to a group of peers and stakeholders

●     Provide technical leadership & expertise across multiple modeling projects

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
What To Expect

The Business Analytics team’s mission is to enable a data driven business and generate values from our data. The team is responsible for providing insights around our business and its associated processes, as well as customers and products. The team directly supports business leaders from our retail locations and at the headquarter, and up to our executive team.

We are looking for a hands-on data scientist who can lead key cross-functional projects for both energy and automotive business using data science tools and techniques to drive business process automations and support sales & service strategies by leveraging our data.

What You’ll Do
Contribute to all the stages of data science projects: from translating a complex business problem into a data science problem to performing data analysis & modeling, and providing solutions to the business.
Develop and maintain complex data pipelines, supporting our team’s mission in democratizing data and enabling a data driven organization, partnering with Data Analysts, Data Engineers, Machine Learning (ML) Engineers, and Product Managers.
Effectively communicate actionable insights to all levels of the organization with varying degree of data science understanding and backgrounds.
Collaborate closely with leadership, engineering, and other stakeholders to deliver impactful business insights.
Apply various ML, advanced analytics and visualization techniques to various datasets across the company.
What You’ll Bring
MS. or 2+ years of equivalent experience in a quantitative field (e.g. Data Science, Applied Mathematics, Business Analytics, Operations Research, Statistics, Computer Science, Artificial Intelligence, Economics or Engineering).
Results oriented with strong business acumen and in-depth data science skills.
Strong written, verbal, and interpersonal communication skills. Ability to communicate effectively at all levels in the organization.
Proven track record of extracting data insights and building ML models and, especially in business analytics (or related) domain. Uplevel team’s ML capabilities in one or more major areas (e.g. forecasting, predictive modeling, descriptive analytics, or Natural Language Processing (NLP)).
Expert in SQL and Python, especially in standard data science libraries and frameworks such as pandas, numpy, scikit-learn, Tensorflow/PyTorch, PySpark, etc.
Proficiency in one or more visualization tools such as Tableau, Streamlit etc.
Expert in data wrangling and analyzing massive and complex datasets, structured or unstructured.
Ability to self-start and work independently in an unstructured environment as well as navigate (and bring structure to) ambiguity, bringing a problem from 0 to 1.
Excellent problem-framing, problem solving and project management skills as well as ability to change direction quickly.
Ability to manage and prioritize multiple projects.


Benefits

Along with competitive pay, as a full-time Tesla employee, you are eligible for the following benefits at day 1 of hire:
Aetna PPO and HSA plans > 2 medical plan options with $0 payroll deduction
Family-building, fertility, adoption and surrogacy benefits
Dental (including orthodontic coverage) and vision plans, both have options with a $0 paycheck contribution
Company Paid (Health Savings Account) HSA Contribution when enrolled in the High Deductible Aetna medical plan with HSA
Healthcare and Dependent Care Flexible Spending Accounts (FSA)
LGBTQ+ care concierge services
401(k) with employer match, Employee Stock Purchase Plans, and other financial benefits
Company paid Basic Life, AD&D, short-term and long-term disability insurance
Employee Assistance Program
Sick and Vacation time (Flex time for salary positions), and Paid Holidays
Back-up childcare and parenting support resources
Voluntary benefits to include: critical illness, hospital indemnity, accident insurance, theft & legal services, and pet insurance
Weight Loss and Tobacco Cessation Programs
Tesla Babies program
Commuter benefits
Employee discounts and perks program


Expected Compensation

$80,000 - $258,000/annual salary + cash and stock awards + benefits

Pay offered may vary depending on multiple individualized factors, including market location, job-related knowledge, skills, and experience. The total compensation package for this position may also include other elements dependent on the position offered. Details of participation in these benefit plans will be provided if an employee receives an offer of employment.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
About The Role

At FINESSE, we pride ourselves in building the foundations of a consumer brain - one that understands consumer preferences and predicts trends. As our Machine Learning Engineer, you will creatively brainstorm new data sources, pipelines and algorithmic strategies to improve our trend prediction and demand forecasting. You will work alongside brilliant members of a world class team to build fascinating technology and you will leverage the latest techniques in AI and machine learning across network analysis, natural language understanding, time series analysis, computer vision and recommendation systems to optimize our decisions on what to design, how much of it to produce, and which rising social media influencers to work with.

About You

You can’t wait to apply your data and machine learning expertise to figure out what’s trending in culture and fashion in realtime and to eliminate the inefficiencies in fashion design and distribution that contribute to fashion being the second largest polluter in the world. You love social data and the messy nature of it and embrace the challenges of big data, performance and scalability, thinking for the long-term and setting up systems that benchmark progress, prevent regressions, and are easily maintainable by other collaborators. Above all, you’re excited to build something from the ground up that will touch the lives of millions of people worldwide.

Recommended Background

Experience working with heavily alternative data sets
Experience across NLP, sentiment analysis, network/graph analysis, time series analysis, reinforcement learning, computer vision with a deep specialization in one area
Solid statistical foundation and inspired creative mathematical understanding of real world problems
Experience building production-level machine learning systems
Knowledge of technologies such as Tensorflow, Keras, Hadoop, Postgres, AWS, Docker

What You’ll Love At FINESSE

Being at the forefront of and working towards creating a culture-defining new product
A close-knit, extremely passionate & world class team excited about changing the face of fashion
A diverse team and culture that values inclusivity and individuality as highest priority
Company sponsored happy hours and outings
Comprehensive benefits: Medical, dental and vision insurance; 401k
Paid maternity and paternity leave
Sponsored weekly team lunches
Unlimited PTO

Our Culture

FINESSE has a dreamer & doer culture. We envision the next age of fashion & consumer and then get to work to implement it, always thinking creatively, innovatively and collaboratively to create real change. We are energetic, highly creative and hungry for change that is both revolutionizing as well as ethical.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Company Description

Afficiency is a rapidly growing Insurtech startup whose mission is to provide life insurance to everyone on the platforms they already trust. Located in NYC, we design life insurance products that can be purchased entirely digitally and can be easily embedded into distribution platforms or with agents who sell insurance. The company is experiencing rapid growth and is well-funded. We are looking for new team members to join us on our journey to shake up the life insurance industry. We need individuals who bring passion, curiosity, and a desire for excellence. 




Job Description

Please note that this job is only hiring candidates that live in the Metro NYC area and are able to commute to the office.

We are seeking a data scientist to join our business intelligence team to help us make better business decisions based on our data. The ideal candidate will have a working knowledge of statistics, mathematics, and data science programming languages (e.g., SQL, R, Python).

Your primary responsibilities will be performing statistical analyses and identifying patterns and trends that can improve our products’ and services’ efficiency and usability. You will also be expected to maintain and improve our data infrastructure and tools.




Qualifications

Work with stakeholders to identify key metrics and opportunities for improving business processes, products, and services
Build, deploy, and maintain data management systems and back-end data infrastructure for our business intelligence pipeline
Perform data mining, exploration, and analysis
Create data visualizations, reports, dashboards, and data audits
Design, train, and implement machine learning algorithms
Leverage predictive models to optimize customer experiences
Creating automated anomaly detection




Requirements

Bachelor's degree in data science, data analytics, or related field
Master’s degree or Ph.D. in a quantitative field, such as statistics, computer science, mathematics, or engineering
Proficiency in Python, Java, or Kotlin
Knowledge of data science toolkits such as R, NumPy, and MatLab
Experience with big data analytics technologies such as Spark and Hadoop
Experience with data visualization tools such as D3.js and Tableau
Expertise in data mining and machine learning
Working knowledge of statistical models and business intelligence
Familiarity with cloud-based infrastructure
Ability to store and process unstructured data with NoSQL databases and machine learning models




Additional Information

What We Offer 

Fully remote work with a flexible schedule
Stipend to purchase work-from-home equipment 
Competitive salary with equity options 
Robust health, dental, and vision benefits for employee and dependents 
401k matching contributions 
Generous PTO policy 
Work at a supportive and fast-growing startup with a fantastic team 
Environment to learn from other team members, grow a business from the ground up 
Support in developing your skills and accelerating your career quickly 
Opportunity to make an impact in the lives of tens of millions of consumers and get families the protection they need 

Afficiency is an Equal Opportunity Employer.

Title: Software Engineer I
Description:
Your Mission




We see boundless potential in the way we live. It drives the way we work. Our culture is our most valuable asset. It acts like a compass for us. We are fast, immersed, humble and bold. And that’s not just words on the walls.




Eliminating time-consuming tasks means people get to do more of what they love. It’s an inspiring, high stakes challenge that motivates us, and this common passion bonds UiPath employees globally. We all strive every day to be better and to accelerate human achievement.




We make software robots, so people don’t have to be robots. Would you like to be part of this journey?




Identity is at the core of the security architecture of any enterprise. To onboard any organization to a SaaS offering, a SaaS solution needs to onboard the users in the organization to use its service is an easy, seamless manner while being compliant and secure. We, at UiPath identity service team, are hiring a SWE to join us on this mission. Our charter is to allow our customers to bring and manage any user with their existing identities (enterprise or consumer) to use UiPath on cloud or on-prem using whatever protocols their existing identity systems use, like OAuth and OpenID Connect, SAML or with on-prem identity systems like AD and ADFS and securely manage user sessions across UiPath services.




We are also the platform service that other UiPath services use to authenticate and authorize users, robots, applications and other internal services and provide critical security features like least privilege, blast radius reduction, offline access and delegation.




If you are looking to work in a fast paced environment, on high scale services servicing millions of requests per day, secure by design, iterating fast, learning and growing quickly as a result, passionate about delivering features that architecturally take our service to the next level in terms of scalability, security and performance, and to expand platform capabilities to newer revenue generating scenarios for our services, we are looking for you!




What You'll Do At UiPath




Our mission is to build a platform for scale and is also easy to consume for our customers. Quality is baked into our DNA and we believe in being agile and gritty.




As a SWE in the platform team, you will




Design and engineer significant areas of the cloud platform to deliver end to end business outcomes.
Ensure UiPath online services are highly available, participate in livesite monitoring rotations, handle escalations, driving effective mitigations, and making continuous improvements to our livesite process.
Ensure our technical deliverables meet or exceed the expectations on reliability, scalability, quality and performance.
Adhere to and influence our best practices across the engineering organization
Ensure UiPath online services are highly available, participate in livesite monitoring rotations, handle escalations, driving effective mitigations, aggressively reducing its live site impact to customers with broad, detailed and effective post mortems.
Participate in task planning, estimation, scheduling




What You'll Bring To The Team




Proficiency in one or more object-oriented languages (such as C#/C++/Java) backed by solid computer science fundamentals
Familiar with modern engineering practices, including agile development, CI/CD and devops. Ability to work with globally distributed teams.
Experience with developing microservice-based HTTP applications and servers
Good grasp of multithreading, synchronization, asynchronous, cloud programming.
Deep understanding of data structures & algorithms.
Experience with service-oriented architecture and web services development.
Experience in using database backends (e.g. Azure SQL, CosmosDB, Azure Datalake, PowerBI, MangoDB, MSQL, or DynamoDB, etc.)
Experience working with or managing production Kubernetes infrastructure is a plus
Experience working with cloud providers like Azure, AWS, Google Cloud, etc. and cloud services such as AKS, GKE, etc. is a plus
Experience working with identity systems (Okta, AAD, Windows AD) and identity protocols (OAuth, OIDC, SAML) is a plus

Title: Junior Software Engineer
Description:
DataBP is looking for a skilled Software Engineer to join our team and create dynamic, high-performance web applications using modern development frameworks like React, Vue.js, and similar tools. We value candidates who possess a flexible mindset and are committed to mastering new technologies to solve problems and deliver outstanding value to our customers. If you're eager to join a thriving FinTech company from its inception, we encourage you to apply for the Software Engineer position today. 

 

As part of our team, you will contribute to the growth of a thriving SaaS company that serves leading financial institutions and exchanges worldwide. We offer a competitive compensation package, ample vacation days, and the added benefit of remote work. Join us today and be part of a team that's making a difference in the financial technology industry. 

 

Responsibilities: 

Develop single-page applications and REST APIs that streamline business process administration for financial companies. 
Deliver pragmatic software solutions that quickly deliver features without sacrificing quality. 
Share new ideas and best practices by providing information architecture skills to prototype new technology concepts and features. 
Assist in maintaining both legacy and current systems, as well as supporting the migration process to modern technology stacks. 

 

Qualifications: 

Strong understanding of JavaScript, HTML, and CSS. 
At least one year of experience working with Vue.js or similar frameworks. 
Experience building lightweight web applications that consume external REST APIs services. 
Familiarity with common development tools such as Git, Webpack, Gulp, SASS, and Yarn/NPM. 
Solid understanding of automated unit, integration, and functional test suites. 
Strong desire to learn, push the envelope, and share knowledge with other engineers across the world. 
Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science/Engineering or 3+ years of relevant experience. 
Passionate about customer focus with the ability to drive system improvements. 

 

Bonus Qualifications: 

Experience with Agile/Scrum methodologies. 
Proficiency with SQL databases, C# or other server-side technologies. 
Strong interpersonal, communication, self-management, and organizational skills. 

 

The wage range for this role takes into account the wide range of factors that are considered in making compensation decisions including but not limited to skill sets; experience and training; licensure and certifications; and other business and organizational needs. It is not typical for an individual to be hired at or near the top of the range for their role and compensation decisions are dependent on the facts and circumstances of each case. A reasonable estimate of the current range is $75,000-$90,000.

Title: Data Scientist, Battery Manufacturing Engineering
Description:
What To Expect
Tesla is looking to hire a Data Scientist to contribute to the development and deployment of specialized manufacturing processes for our cutting-edge vehicle battery products. In this position, you will have access to data playgrounds across manufacturing processes and equipment globally and the opportunity to build and implement innovative data science services, models, and tools into production use. Battery development is at the heart of our company, and this is an exciting opportunity to work directly on the central challenges with electric vehicles – battery cost and performance. Tesla is a demanding and fast-paced environment where you will work with a highly motivated team on extremely challenging projects.
What You’ll Do
Perform exploratory analyses and correlation studies on process-related inputs and outputs to facilitate the understanding of process mechanisms
Act as the owner/subject matter expert to collect and analyze data, identify process improvement opportunities, inform solution spaces, and drive the evaluation of their effectiveness
Develop and deploy sophisticated algorithms and predictive models using in-process and post-process data to improve manufacturing process monitoring/part quality prediction capability
Clearly convey results of data analyses in a way that is digestible by cross-functional stakeholders to facilitate the rapid development and deployment of solutions
Standardize the reporting architecture of key manufacturing line performance metrics (OEE, etc.) across various stations and processes
Determine what data should be collected and how on new manufacturing process and production lines
Develop frameworks and methodologies for experimental design (A/B test, RCA, GRRs, etc.)
Research and evaluate external data acquisition & processing software for process monitoring


What You’ll Bring
BS, and/or MS in quantitative fields (Statistics, Data Science, Applied Mathematics, etc.)
1+ years of experience in manipulating and analyzing complex & high-volume data from various sources
Proficiency with programming languages such as Python, R
Proficiency with relational and/or non-relational databases
Proficiency with data visualization techniques and tools using Tableau, R Shiny, Python Dash, Plotly, etc.
Strong mathematical/ statistical knowledge relevant to process control and monitoring
Experience with experimental design is a plus
Experience working with high-volume manufacturing data streams is a strong plus


Benefits

Along with competitive pay, as a full-time Tesla employee, you are eligible for the following benefits at day 1 of hire:
Aetna PPO and HSA plans > 2 medical plan options with $0 payroll deduction
Family-building, fertility, adoption and surrogacy benefits
Dental (including orthodontic coverage) and vision plans, both have options with a $0 paycheck contribution
Company Paid (Health Savings Account) HSA Contribution when enrolled in the High Deductible Aetna medical plan with HSA
Healthcare and Dependent Care Flexible Spending Accounts (FSA)
LGBTQ+ care concierge services
401(k) with employer match, Employee Stock Purchase Plans, and other financial benefits
Company paid Basic Life, AD&D, short-term and long-term disability insurance
Employee Assistance Program
Sick and Vacation time (Flex time for salary positions), and Paid Holidays
Back-up childcare and parenting support resources
Voluntary benefits to include: critical illness, hospital indemnity, accident insurance, theft & legal services, and pet insurance
Weight Loss and Tobacco Cessation Programs
Tesla Babies program
Commuter benefits
Employee discounts and perks program


Expected Compensation

$76,000 - $276,000/annual salary + cash and stock awards + benefits

Pay offered may vary depending on multiple individualized factors, including market location, job-related knowledge, skills, and experience. The total compensation package for this position may also include other elements dependent on the position offered. Details of participation in these benefit plans will be provided if an employee receives an offer of employment.

Description:
Integrating large data sets to develop pricing data and machine learning models, build machine learning algorithms, and incorporate outcomes into various systems and tools. Preferred: 3+ years relevant experience in a data science role related to pricing
Required: 3+ years relevant experience in a data science role
Ability to multi-task, manage tight deadlines, handle competing priorities and achieve results in a dynamic environment
Skilled in managing complex projects that require working with cross-functional teams
Strong communication and presentation skills with experience in summarizing complex information and adapting message to different audiences
Passionate about working with large sets of complex data and finding relationships to uncover insights
Strong analytical skills with a keen attention to detail and ability to recognize patterns and anomalies

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Description

Leidos is looking for a candidate to support survey design, development, implementation, and analysis, as well as running focus groups, and briefing results to customer stakeholders. Surveys will focus on issues related to customer workforce perceptions and morale on topics such as communication, diversity and inclusion, promotion selection, and management support. This involves using customer-provided survey tools. Some surveys will be part of a continuing series that provides an ability to see trends over time.

The office provides business analytics primarily using structured datasets, but values surveys to fill in knowledge gaps that structured data does not provide. The successful candidate should be someone who is creative and independent, and is capable of managing many tasks at the same time. The candidate needs to have excellent communications skills and be capable of imparting insights orally and through written analytic products.

Primary Responsibilities

Consult with customer stakeholders to frame survey design and create responsive questions.
Create and run surveys in customer-provided applications.
Run focus groups to generate more in-depth data and analyze that data in conjunction with survey data.
Direct, manage, and mentor junior team members.
Collaborate cross-functionally with other team members, such as methodologists and database developers, to compile survey results, including through online dashboards.

Basic Qualifications

BS degree and 12 – 15 years of prior relevant experience or Masters with 10 – 13 years of prior relevant experience.
At least 8+ years of relevant work experience.
Ability to work across multidisciplinary teams.
Experience with PowerPoint, Word, and Excel.
Active TS/SCI with a polygraph

Preferred Qualifications

Experience working with MS Access, SQL Server or Oracle databases and with Tableau or Power BI dashboard software.
Experience with Intelligence Community workforce and with issues unique to that environment.

Pay Range

Pay Range $142,350.00 - $219,000.00 - $295,650.00

The Leidos pay range for this job level is a general guideline only and not a guarantee of compensation or salary. Additional factors considered in extending an offer include (but are not limited to) responsibilities of the job, education, experience, knowledge, skills, and abilities, as well as internal equity, alignment with market data, applicable bargaining agreement (if any), or other law.

Title: Artificial Intelligence Engineer
Description:
About the Job

Spatial Labs makes the hardware+software that powers the Web3 economy. We build ecosystems with real-world value and utility, making blockchain and the metaverse accessible and usable for the masses.




We have raised $14m in seed funding from notable VCs such as JAY-Z from Marcy Ventures, Blockchain Capital, and more. Link to raise details.




Spatial Labs currently powers infrastructure for brands such as Tidal, Pantone, IKEA, CROCS, ALES GREY, and more.




Spatial Labs is seeking an experienced Artificial Intelligence (AI) Engineer with a focus on wearable products to join the Spatial Labs team. The AI Engineer will be responsible for designing, developing, and implementing AI algorithms and models for wearable products. The ideal candidate should have a strong background in machine learning, deep learning, computer vision, and data analysis, as well as experience in developing and deploying AI models on wearables.


Responsibilities

Design, develop, and implement AI algorithms and models for wearable products.
Develop and optimize machine learning and deep learning models for wearable products.
Implement computer vision algorithms on wearable devices to improve user experience.
Analyze and interpret large data sets from wearable devices to derive meaningful insights.
Work closely with the software development team to integrate AI models into wearable products.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including hardware engineers, product managers, and designers, to deliver high-quality wearable products.
Stay up-to-date with the latest research and advancements in AI, machine learning, and wearable technology.


Experience and Qualifications

Qualifications:

Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, or a related field.
3+ years of experience in AI, machine learning, and deep learning.
Strong programming skills in Python, C++, and/or Java.
Experience with popular machine learning and deep learning frameworks such as GPT , TensorFlow, Keras, PyTorch, and Scikit-learn.
Experience with computer vision and image processing algorithms.
Knowledge of wearable technology and its design principles.
Ability to analyze and interpret large data sets.
Strong problem-solving skills and ability to work independently or in a team environment.
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.

Preferred:

Experience with developing and deploying AI models on wearable products.
Knowledge of signal processing and sensor fusion techniques for wearable products.
Familiarity with embedded systems and microcontrollers.
Experience with mobile app development.




If you are a self-starter who is passionate about using AI to develop innovative wearable products and are looking for an exciting new opportunity, we encourage you to apply. We offer a competitive salary, flexible work hours, and a dynamic and collaborative work environment.
